HEADWORD: Conative
<hw>Co"na*tive</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Conatus</er>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to conation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This division of mind into the three great classes of the
cognitive faculties, the feelings, . . . and the exertive or
<qex>conative</qex> powers, . . . was first promulgated by Kant.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

